<br>
Well depending on exactly how it is implemented. It could eliminate a significant barrier to mastering tradeskills. The sheer number of clicks and mouse moving that tradeskills currently require is a big turn off for many people. <br>
<br>
Easier tradeskills means more people doing them. Which in turn means a Higher demand on raw materials. This could cause prices on those raw components to skyrocket. You think people charge outrageous prices for a flawless rockhopper hides, acrylia, velium,  or morning dew now you may be in for  a surprise.<br>
<br>
On the other side of the coin more master craftspeople means more competition. More finished product available Which will drive down the prices of finished goods. Now this is a good thing for the consumer but not so good for the tradeskiller trying to make any kind of profit or return on their skill.<br>
<br>
As I said earlier there are ways to implement what they want to do without causing those things I mentioned above from happening so its more of a wait and see what they are actually going to do. This has the potential to be the best thing to happen to tradeskills or the worst.<br>
<br>
<br>
